Title: Click or Call? Auction versus Search in the Over-the-Counter Market 
Author-Name: TERRENCE HENDERSHOTT  
Author-Name: ANANTH MADHAVAN  
Abstract:
  type="main"> <title type="main">ABSTRACT</title> <p>Over-the-counter
 (OTC) markets dominate trading in many asset classes. Will electronic
 trading displace traditional OTC “voice” trading? Can electronic and voice
 systems coexist? What types of securities and trades are best suited for
 electronic trading? We study these questions by focusing on an innovation
 in electronic trading technology that enables investors to simultaneously
 search many bond dealers. We show that periodic one-sided electronic
 auctions are a viable and important source of liquidity even in inactively
 traded instruments. These mechanisms are a natural compromise between
 bilateral search in OTC markets and continuous double auctions in
 electronic limit order books.
